entry.content:
Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.title: Austin J. Tobin Plaza (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the Austin J. Tobin Plaza (pictured) was destroyed in the September 11 attacks, but one of the sculptures on it survived?

entry.title: Motibai Kapadia (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that in 1884 Motibai Kapadia's father allowed her to study alongside men in India?

entry.title: steam tug Brent (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that in the late 1940s the steam tug Brent removed war-related debris, including naval mines, from the River Thames?

entry.title: Lorena Peril (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Lorena Peril, who once cleaned toilets at a nursing home, beat out over 3,000 people to sing the national anthem for the San Francisco 49ers?

entry.title: died following a dog attack (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Mohammad Bhar, a Palestinian man with Down syndrome and autism, died following a dog attack in the Gaza Strip during the Israel–Hamas war?

entry.title: The Eternaut (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Héctor Germán Oesterheld repurposed his initial plans for a sequel of the comic The Eternaut as a novel?

entry.title: Helen Hornbeck Tanner (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Helen Hornbeck Tanner was part of a major case supporting the Ojibwe before the Supreme Court of the United States while in her 80s?

entry.title: Wolfman's Got Nards (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the title of the documentary Wolfman's Got Nards is derived from a memorable line in the 1987 film The Monster Squad?

entry.title: Jajaira Gonzalez (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that USA Boxing's head coach said that Olympian Jajaira Gonzalez's return to boxing was "like Lazarus coming back from the dead"?
